{"lemma":"رِيحِ","slug":"رِيحِ","root":"ر.#.ح","root_slug":"ر-_-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-_-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رِيح","root":"روح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":29},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16988"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AD%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wind","examples":[{"text":"هُوَ ٱلَّذِي يُسَيِّرُكُمْ فِي ٱلْبَرِّ وَٱلْبَحْرِ ۖ حَتَّى إِذَا كُنْتُمْ فِي ٱلْفُلْكِ وَجَرَيْنَ بِهِم بِرِيحٍ طَيِّبَةٍ وَفَرِحُوا۟ بِهَا جَاءَتْهَا رِيحٌ عَاصِفٌ وَجَاءَهُمُ ٱلْمَوْجُ مِن كُلِّ مَكَانٍ وَظَنُّوا۟ أَنَّهُمْ أُحِيطَ بِهِمْ ۙ دَعَوُا۟ ٱللَّهَ مُخْلِصِينَ لَهُ ٱلدِّينَ لَئِنْ أَنْجَيْتَنَا مِنْ هَٰذِهِ لَنَكُونَنَّ مِنَ ٱلشَّاكِرِينَ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fart"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"smell, odor"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"windy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ease, to comfort, to relax"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *rīḥ-.\n\nLess intensive a causative than أَرَاحَ (ʔarāḥa). Note that yy instead of ww is very regular, medial و (w) in form II verbs from roots mediae waw are found in Arabic only by analogical root restoration.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/riːħ/","/raj.jiħ/","/raj.ja.ħa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16988","headword_ar":"رِيحٌ","root":"rwH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riwoHN","text_ar":"رِوْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the preceding kesreh, (T, S, Msb,) as is shown by its dim. mentioned below; (T, Msb;) Sb held it to be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolN","text_ar":"فِعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1181},{"kind":"text","text":"Abu-l-Hasan,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolN","text_ar":"فِعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolN","text_ar":"فُعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [if the latter, originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruyoHN","text_ar":"رُيْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] (TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"air that is made to obey"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the will of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and to run its course between heaven and earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breath"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiym","text_ar":"نَسِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the air;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of anything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) said to be thus called because it generally brings"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoH","text_ar":"رَوْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHap","text_ar":"رَاحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. rest, or ease]: (IAmb, MF:) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHapN","text_ar":"رِيحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN","text_ar":"دَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArapN","text_ar":"دَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [using the latter as a more special term; for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHapN","text_ar":"رِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion of wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^ifapN mino riyHK","text_ar":"طَايِفَةٌ مِنْ رِيحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":") [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wind of short duration;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a breath, puff, blast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gust, of wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Sb, M;) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHapN","text_ar":"رِيحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be used in the same sense; i. e. the latter may be used as syn. with the former, and they are mentioned by some [as analogous] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawokabN","text_ar":"كَوْكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawokabapN","text_ar":"كَوْكَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, L:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyoH","text_ar":"رِيْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the fem. gender (IAmb, L, Msb) in most cases; (Msb;) and all the other names for wind are fem. except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEoSaArN","text_ar":"اـِعْصَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is masc.; (IAmb, Msb;) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ryH","text_ar":"ريح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes made masc. as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawaA='N","text_ar":"هَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, Msb:) [it is used by physicians as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flatus, flatuosity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flatulence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN galiyZapN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ غَلِيظَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gross flatus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowaAHN","text_ar":"اَرْوَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroyaAHN","text_ar":"اَرْيَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the latter used by some, but disallowed by AHát because there is in it no kesreh to cause the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,) and [the pl. of mult. is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaAHN","text_ar":"رِيَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the kesreh, (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaHN","text_ar":"رِيَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, but not found by SM in any other lexicon;) and the pl. pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAwiyHu","text_ar":"اَرَاوِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowaAHN","text_ar":"اَرْوَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAyiyHu","text_ar":"اَرَايِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroyaAHN","text_ar":"اَرْيَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwayoHapN","text_ar":"رُوَيْحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaAHN","text_ar":"رِيَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or another form of pl., is often used in a good sense; and the sing., in an evil sense; because the Arabs say that the clouds are not made to give rain save by diverse winds blowing together; and this distinction is observed in the Kur-án. (L.) Hence, it is related in a trad., that he [Mohammad] used to say, when wind rose,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a A@joEalohaA riyaAHFA wa laA tajoEalohaA riyHFA","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ ا@جْعَلْهَا رِيَاحًا وَ لَا تَجْعَلْهَا رِيحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, make it to be winds, and made it not to be a wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [But this distinction is not always observed.] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yamiylu maEa kul~i","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَمِيلُ مَعَ كُلِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHK","text_ar":"رِيحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one inclines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turns, with every wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN kaAlr~iyHi Almurosalapi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ كَالرِّيحِ المُرْسَلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is like the wind that is sent forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"to drive the clouds, and produce rain; (see the Kur xxv. 50;)] meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prompt, to do acts of kindness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN saAkinu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ سَاكِنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHi","text_ar":"الرِّيحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is calm, sedate, staid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grave."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Predominance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prevalence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"force."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) A poet says, (S,) namely, Suleyk Ibn-Es-Sulakeh, or Taäbbata-Sharrà, or Aashà of the tribe of Fahm, (TA, and so in one of my copies of the S,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^atanoZuraAni qaliylFA rayova gafolatihimo\n                      \n                     \n                        A^awo taEoduwaAni faA_in~a Alr~iyHa liloEaAdiY"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Will ye two await, a little, the time of their inadvertence, or will ye act aggressively? for prevalence is for the aggressor"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And hence the phrase in the Kur [viii. 48],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa ta*ohaba","text_ar":"وَ تَذْهَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHukumo","text_ar":"رِيحُكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And your predominance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power, depart"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) [or in this latter instance it has the meaning next following.] ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aid against an enemy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"victory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conquest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a turn of good fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabato riyHuhumo","text_ar":"ذَهَبَتْ رِيحُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their turn of good fortune departed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA hab~ato riyaAHuka faA@gotanimohaA","text_ar":"اـِذَا هَبَّتْ رِيَاحُكَ فَا@غْتَنِمْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When thy turns of good fortune come, avail thyself of them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHu liA=li fulaAnK","text_ar":"الرِّيحُ لِا=لِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aid against the enemy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"victory"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conquest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the turn of good fortune, is to the family of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoHN","text_ar":"رَوْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iHapN","text_ar":"رَايِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(with which it is syn.), in four places. ―         -b6-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good, sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant, thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b7-  The pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowaAHN","text_ar":"اَرْوَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a trad. as meaning (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they are [supposed to be often] invisible, like the wind. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","Msb","TA","L","IAmb","MF","Sb","AZ","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}